As Peik Lin's car approached the porte cochere of Tyersall Park, 
Nicholas Young bounded down the front steps. 
"I was worried you’d gotten lost," he said, opening the car door. 
"We did get a bit lost, actually," Rachel replied. 
"For some strange reason, your grandmother’s house didn’t 
show up on my GPS," said Peik Lin, who prided herself 
on knowing every street in Singapore. 
Rachel got out of the car and stared up at 
the majestic facade before her. "Am I really late?"
